    "sn1.10:3.1": "Compare <a href='https://suttacentral.net/mn131/en/sujato#3.1'>MN 131:3.1</a>. ",
    "sn1.10:3.2": "<i lang='pi' translate='no'>Pajappanti </i>, from <i lang='pi' translate='no'>jappa</i>, means both to “incant” and to “long for”, and the English “pray’ has exactly the same connotations—for exactly the same reasons. They originated in begging favors of a god. "
  },
